    thinking: "**Defining the View\'s Scope**\n\nI\'m focusing now on defining the scope of `src/components/MLDashboard.tsx`. It\'s clear this view needs to explain an automatic update process, specifically addressing how the user, the business owner in this case, can add or modify purchase transactions directly. I am currently evaluating the user\'s requirements so the user will be properly guided.\n\n\n**Implementing Real-Time Updates**\n\nI\'m now implementing the real-time update functionality within the dashboard. I\'ve designed a multi-line f-string to display key metrics like active records, decision tree/KNN scores, and a Plotly chart SVG. Further updates include advanced Pandas filtering for the \'Osorno Centro\' branch, grouping by \'fuga\' state and calculating monthly spending/visits. Finally, I\'m simulating transaction addition via a form to `/api/ml-analysis/simulate` for a truly dynamic user experience.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will now create the file `/src/components/MLDashboard.tsx`. This file displays the advanced data-science and machine learning analytics. It features:\n1. **Dynamic Vector Scatter Plot**: Generates and renders the live SVG block calculated by the backend showing monthly expenditures vs visits, colored by churn (fuga) state.\n2. **Pandas Filtration & Aggregation**: Details the filtered mean spending and visits exclusively for the \"Osorno Centro\" branch.\n3. **Parallel ML Models (KNN & Decision Tree)**: Tracks the live accuracy rates derived on the fly from the current database records.\n4. **Live Multiline Python f-ring**: Prints out the formatted string with relational values.\n5. **Interactive Laragon simulation**: Allows the owner to insert a mock transaction dynamically, illustrating exactly how the dashboard adapts in seconds without needing to rewrite any HTML or refresh the application.\n6. **Integration Reference Codes**: Features copy-pasteable, pure Python scripts utilizing `mysql.connector`, `pandas`, `sklearn`, and `plotly.express` to replicate the process local-side!"
